<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25829</anchor> <rss>anon.210.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.210</addr>  <route>anon.210.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>This follows immediately from the fact that <link href="jms-006M.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006M" title="Disjoint coproducts are independent sums">independent sums are coproducts</link> in extensive <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25830</anchor> <rss>jms-006Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-006Q</addr>  <route>jms-006Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Independent complements in extensive categories</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>In an extensive category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>, the independent complement of a monomorphism is precisely the Heyting complement of that morphism when it exists.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25831</anchor> <rss>jms-006M.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-006M</addr>  <route>jms-006M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Disjoint coproducts are independent sums</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>In an extensive category, any coproduct co-span <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ u  \hookrightarrow  u+v  \hookleftarrow  v \right \} \mathclose {}}</tex> is an <link href="jms-006L.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006L" title="Independent sum">independent sum</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25832</anchor> <rss>anon.212.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.212</addr>  <route>anon.212.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As soon as the co-span <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ u  \hookrightarrow  u+v  \hookleftarrow  v \right \} \mathclose {}}</tex> is independent, it evidently satisfies the universal property of <link href="jms-006L.xml" type="local" addr="jms-006L" title="Independent sum">independent sums</link>, which is weaker than that of coproducts. Coproduct co-spans are always independent in an extensive category.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>